      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the face ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "as a second object—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "shame hath covered me as to my face, i.e., covered my face. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Though the record of the facts of a sad reality, these verses have also the value of a prophecy sadder still. Twenty centuries of misery are summed up in these few lines, which have been most literally repeated,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "“By the torture, prolonged from age to age,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "By the infamy, Israel’s heritage;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "By the Ghetto’s plague, by the garb’s disgrace,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "By the badge of shame, by the felon’s place.”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "R. BROWNING: Holy Cross Day.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "R. BROWNING: ",
            "children": []
